==English==
===Noun===
'''last straw'''

#{{slang}} A small additional burden that when added to an already large burden causes it to exceed the capacity.  From the expression "It's the '''last straw''' that breaks the camel's back", meaning that you can load a camel wuith a heavy load, but adding even a little (a single [[straw]]) can be more than it can handle causing a disasterous consequence.  
#:''That's the '''last straw''', it's a [[petty]] demand but I'm already under too much work.  I quit!"